Distillers grains are a cereal byproduct of the distillation process traditionally produced by breweries and more recently by ethanol plants.

Distillers grains are created in distilleries by drying mash, and is subsequently sold for a variety of purposes, usually as fodder for livestock (especially ruminants). Corn-based distillers grains from the ethanol industry are commonly sold as a high protein livestock feed that increases efficiency and lowers the risk of subacute acidosis in beef cattle.
